  "title" : "Source root is duplicated in module ... error in IntelliJ Idea",
  "body" : "<p>I'm working on a large Maven project in IntelliJ Idea. Java version is 8. When I build the project it fails with this output:</p>\n<pre><code>java Modules ACClient and FdsxClient must have the same language level because of cyclic dependencies between them\n    In the *Project Structure -&gt; Project Settings -&gt; Project*\nSDK value is 1.8 Oracle OpenJDK\nLanguage level value is 8 - Lambdas, type annotations etc.\n    In the *Project Structure -&gt; Project Settings -&gt; Modules*\n</code></pre>\n<p>Language level for ACClient is 8 - Lambdas, type annotations etc.  (as expected).<br />\nLanguage level for FdsxClient is 6 - @Override in interfaces (this is the problem).<br/></p>\n<p>So I change the wrong one but when I click the apply button an error dialog shows up.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Source root\n'C:\\workspace\\largeJavaProject_r\\abacus\\ACClient\\src\\main\\java' is\nduplicated in module 'AbcClient'.<br/></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Rebuilding project and Maven -&gt; Reload project does not help.</p>\n"
}